## 15. Boolean Filtering

```python
scores = np.array([45, 72, 88, 51, 90, 67])
```

Create a Boolean mask:

```python
mask = scores >= 60
```

Result:

```text
[False, True, True, False, True, True]
```

Apply the mask:

```python
passing_scores = scores[mask]
```

Result:

```text
[72, 88, 90, 67]
```

This can be written directly:

```python
passing_scores = scores[scores >= 60]
```

---

### Multiple Conditions

Select values between 60 and 80:

```python
selected = scores[(scores >= 60) & (scores <= 80)]
```

Use:

```text
& for element-wise AND
| for element-wise OR
~ for element-wise NOT
```

Do not use normal Python `and` with NumPy arrays.

