## 23. Time Complexity

Let:

* (n) = number of students
* (m) = number of features

Validation scans the dataset:

[
O(nm)
]

Feature averages:

[
O(nm)
]

Final-score calculation:

[
O(n)
]

Classification:

[
O(n)
]

Pass-rate calculation:

[
O(n)
]

Because the number of features is fixed at three:

[
m = 3
]

The overall complexity simplifies to:

[
\boxed{O(n)}
]

The program stores arrays containing results for each student:

[
\boxed{O(n)}
]

additional space.

Vectorization does not change the theoretical Big-O complexity, but it generally reduces Python-level overhead.

